msgid ""
"<ol><li>A newly installed app has its default dashboard set to this "
"dashboard i.e. the <i>About</i> dashboard.</li><li>You may wish to set "
"the app's default dashboard to a different dashboard, for example, to the"
" Overview dashboard. In this case, navigate to the <b>menu &gt; Overview "
"&gt; Syslog Overview</b> and at the top right click <b>Edit (or with "
"later Splunk version click the ellipsis button) &gt; Set as Home "
"Dashboard</b>\n"
"          </li><li>If you do set the default dashboard to a dashboard "
"other than the <i>About</i> dashboard, then when you upgrade this app you"
" will not be automatically directed to the <i>About</i> dashboard, so "
"after an upgrade remember to navigate to the <i>About</i> dashboard for "
"the latest information.</li></ol>"
msgstr ""

#. html
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/cylance_protect/local/data/ui/views/About.xml:51
msgid ""
"<p>BlackBerry Cylance provides support for the CylancePROTECT Application"
" for Splunk, but does <b>not</b> support Splunk-specific troubleshooting."
" <b>An existing, healthy Splunk environment is assumed.</b>\n"
"        </p><p>The following self-service resources are available to "
"assist with using the app:</p><ul><li>A detailed installation and usage "
"guide is available here: <a "
"href=\"https://support.cylance.com/s/article/ka044000000Ct64AAC"
"/CylancePROTECT-Application-for-"
"Splunk59\">https://support.cylance.com/s/article/ka044000000Ct64AAC"
"/CylancePROTECT-Application-for-Splunk59</a>\n"
"          </li><li>A slideshow tour with a brief introduction to the app:"
" <a "
"href=\"/app/cylance_protect/About?earliest=0&amp;latest=&amp;tour=cylance\">click"
" here to launch the app tour</a>\n"
"          </li></ul><h3>Support Cases</h3><p>BlackBerry Cylance provides "
"support for this app through MyAccount. Please follow the instructions "
"here to contact the support team: <a "
"href=\"https://support.blackberry.com/kb/articleDetail?language=en_US&amp;articleNumber=000068846\""
" "
"target=\"_blank\">https://support.blackberry.com/kb/articleDetail?language=en_US&amp;articleNumber=000068846</a>"
"\n"
"        </p><h3>Request Guidelines</h3><p>When contacting us for support,"
" please supply the following information:</p><ol><li>CylancePROTECT "
"Splunk App version (look in app.conf)</li><li>Splunk version (e.g. Splunk"
" Enterprise 6.3.3)</li><li>Operation System and version</li><li>Company "
"name</li><li>Description: Of the feature, the feature enhancement (which "
"feature and how to invoke it e.g. the menu items clicked to arrive at a "
"dashboard); or the bug (how to reproduce the issue and describe the "
"expected behavior versus the actual (suspected erroneous) "
"behavior</li><li>Supporting information: screenshot(s), log "
"file(s)</li></ol>"
msgstr ""

